article.headline: Western Michigan 73, IUPUI 72
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Stane's Bufford scored 21 points to tie a career high and lead Western Michigan to a 73-72 victory over IUPUI on Saturday. IUPUI's George Hill also tied a career high, scoring 26 points for the Jaguars (3-5). He scored 18 of his points, including 10 free throws, in the second half. A free throw by Andrew Hershberger with 1:46 left provided the winning point for Western (2-3), which broke a three-game losing streak. IUPUI, which nearly overcame a 12-point deficit, trimmed Western's lead to one point and had the ball with 5.5 seconds left. But David Barlow brought the ball upcourt and was unable to get a shot off before the game-ending buzzer sounded. Hershberger had a double-double, scoring 15 points and grabbing a career-high 12 rebounds. Brian Snider had a game-high nine assists for the Broncos. IUPUI's Brandon Cole had his first double-double of the season, scoring 17 points and totaling 11 rebounds. Matt Burks added 15 points for the Jaguars. Western's bench outscored IUPUI's bench, 18-5, led by six points each from Shawntes Gary and Wes deVries.
